From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Richards <electrodeyt@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Fix shared library linking on sysv4-mlibc

The generic sysv4 GCC path uses -h directly in the compiler driver
command. Our GCC does not accept that Solaris-style option itself; add
a narrower mlibc case that passes the soname option through to the
linker instead while leaving existing sysv4 configurations unchanged.
---
 support/shobj-conf | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/support/shobj-conf b/support/shobj-conf
index c3df351..a307442 100644
--- a/support/shobj-conf
+++ b/support/shobj-conf
@@ -376,6 +376,14 @@ hpux11*)
 	;;
 
+sysv4*-mlibc-*gcc*)
+	SHOBJ_CFLAGS=-fPIC
+	SHOBJ_LDFLAGS='-shared -Wl,-soname,$@'
+	SHOBJ_LD='${CC}'
+
+	SHLIB_LIBVERSION='$(SHLIB_LIBSUFF).$(SHLIB_MAJOR)'
+	;;
+
 sysv4*-*gcc*)
 	SHOBJ_CFLAGS=-shared
 	SHOBJ_LDFLAGS='-shared -h $@'
 	SHOBJ_LD='${CC}'
-- 
